HEADWORD: Inenarrable
<hw>In`e*nar"ra*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>inenarrabilis</ets>; pref. <ets>in-</ets> not +
<ets>enarrabilis</ets> that may be related; fr. <ets>enarrare</ets> to
relate: cf. F. <ets>in⟦eacute⟧narrable</ets>. See
<er>Enarration</er>.]</ety> <def>Incapable of being narrated;
indescribable; ineffable.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Inenarrable</xex> goodness.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Bp.
